cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MA

Reasoning: 
- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper discusses the allocation of display inventory, which can be viewed as a game between advertisers and publishers. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents a computational model for optimization, which involves algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the uncertainty of the supply of Internet viewers, which can be addressed using machine learning techniques. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the theoretical upper and lower bounds, which can be viewed as information-theoretic quantities. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper discusses the allocation of display inventory, which involves multiple agents (advertisers and publishers) interacting with each other.
